summary: Big tech companies are richer than ever and Wall Street is happy. But they're still laying off thousands of workers

headline: Oil Prices Slide as Investors Bet on Output Hike
summary: Oil prices were falling again on Thursday, with OPEC+ set to meet this weekend. The cartel is considering pumping out more crude, Reuters reported Wednesday, citing people familiar with the discussions.

headline: US oil giant ConocoPhillips will lay off up to 25% of its global workforce
summary: The U.S. oil giant announced layoffs as crude futures prices have decreased by about 11% this year.
